The article provides an update on the situation in Greece from White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs. The President has been regularly briefed on the situation in Greece and the markets. Secretary Geithner and Director Summers have briefed the President on the situation in Europe and the markets. The Treasury Department is closely monitoring the situation. The President has spoken with Prime Minister Papandreou and welcomed the reform program announced by the Greek authorities, as well as the support from the IMF and Eurozone members. The President and Secretary Geithner have been in contact with European leaders regarding the situation in Greece. Greece is implementing major economic reforms with the support of the Euro-area and the IMF. The US strongly supports these efforts to restore stability to Greece and confidence in the global financial system.